OL,3,CNo and low-alcohol beer soaring in
OL,4,Cpopularity, pubs report
OL,6,FNo and low-alcohol beers are soaring
OL,7,Fin popularity as 86% of pubs offer the
OL,8,Falternative to become "even more
OL,9,Finclusive", figures show.
OL,11,FPubs are expected to sell a record 140
OL,12,Fmillion pints of low and no-alcohol
OL,13,Fbeer across the UK this year, up from
OL,14,Fmore than 120 million last year, or
OL,15,F12% of all sales for that year alone
OL,16,Fand up by 14% on 2022.
OL,18,FAmong the 86% of pubs now serving no
OL,19,Fand low-alcohol beer, 8% are serving
OL,20,Fit on draught, up from just 2% in 2019.
